4.4 Subsystem 4: Trust & Validation
4.4.1 Responsibilities
•	Evaluate extraction trustworthiness
•	Detect anomalies and duplicates
•	Trigger human validation workflows
•	Approve or reject extracted values

4.4.2 Trust Scoring Model
Trust score = weighted sum of:
•	OCR confidence
•	Extraction confidence
•	Document quality score
•	Completeness score
•	Cross-source consistency
•	Validator approval history
Example trust scoring formula:
TrustScore = 0.35*OCR + 0.25*Extraction + 0.15*Completeness +
             0.15*Consistency + 0.10*DocQuality

4.4.3 Validation Workflow Design (HITL)
Workflow states:
•	PENDING_EXTRACTION
•	PENDING_VALIDATION
•	APPROVED
•	REJECTED
•	NEEDS_RESCAN
•	ESCALATED
Validation object:
{
  "validation_id": "VAL-002",
  "record_object_id": "SRO-919",
  "assigned_to": "validator_007",
  "status": "PENDING_VALIDATION",
  "fields_to_validate": ["invoice_number", "amount", "supplier_name"]
}

4.4.4 Multi-Approver Design
For sensitive datasets:
•	2-step or 3-step approval process
•	compliance officer final signoff

