4.6 Subsystem 6: Knowledge Synchronization & Entity Resolution
4.6.1 Responsibilities
•	Deduplicate records
•	Merge into golden records
•	Build knowledge graph relationships
•	Synchronize with enterprise systems

4.6.2 Entity Resolution Design
Matching criteria:
•	Exact match (ID number, passport number)
•	Fuzzy match (names, addresses)
•	Graph-based match (shared documents, shared phone numbers)
Resolution outputs:
•	MATCHED
•	POSSIBLE_MATCH
•	NO_MATCH
•	NEEDS_HUMAN_REVIEW
Example:
{
  "candidate_a": "PERSON-001",
  "candidate_b": "PERSON-102",
  "match_score": 0.89,
  "status": "POSSIBLE_MATCH"
}

4.6.3 Golden Record Merge Rules
Rules:
•	ID number is authoritative if verified
•	Most recent validated address is selected
•	Multiple phone numbers can coexist
Golden record object:
{
  "golden_person_id": "GP-001",
  "merged_from": ["PERSON-001", "PERSON-102"],
  "fields": {
    "name": "John Doe",
    "national_id": "63-111111A",
    "address": "Harare"
  }
}

4.6.4 Knowledge Graph Model
Graph nodes:
•	Person
•	Organization
•	Document
•	Asset
•	Transaction
•	Case
Graph edges:
•	OWNS
•	WORKS_FOR
•	PAID_TO
•	SIGNED
•	REGISTERED_BY
•	LOCATED_AT
Graph storage:
•	Neo4j recommended for MVP

